From Scott J Costanzo Subject Re RFI Art of clutchless shifting I used to drive a truck a few years I once rode with an old codger that had been driving for about The only time he would use the clutch was to get the truck He could shift that speed lightning quick up or down without the slightest rake of a He was as smooth as It was the most amazing shifting demonstration I've ever seen Having said all that I still don't know why anyone would want to shift a synchronized tranny without a clutch Why do it